WEBVTT

00:05.088 --> 00:06.214
Previously, on
"Below Deck Mediterranean"...

00:07.424 --> 00:09.467
Being back on the
Dalmatian Coast

00:09.509 --> 00:11.803
based in Sibenik,
it's nature, country.

00:11.845 --> 00:12.804
I love that.

00:12.846 --> 00:13.805
-Hi!
-Welcome back.

00:13.847 --> 00:15.223
Thank you!

00:15.265 --> 00:16.266
-Lloyd? Malia.
-Yeah. Nice to meet you.

00:16.307 --> 00:17.475
Nice to meet you.

00:17.517 --> 00:19.060
-I'm Lexi.
-I'm Katie.

00:19.102 --> 00:20.478
-Where are you from?
-I'm from Bahamas.

00:20.520 --> 00:23.523
I was Miss Bahamas,
but I don't tell people.

00:23.565 --> 00:25.191
I did a Miss Bahamas pageant.

00:25.233 --> 00:26.443
Wow.

00:26.484 --> 00:28.111
-Hey, Z.
-Hey...

00:30.280 --> 00:32.532
I didn't realize
Z was that green.

00:32.574 --> 00:35.118
Is this your first boat?

00:35.160 --> 00:37.120
I'll have you on lates,
I'll stay on mids.

00:37.162 --> 00:39.039
I do wanna rotate.

00:39.080 --> 00:41.291
I don't consider myself
a typical chief stew.

00:41.332 --> 00:43.376
I think you get more
out of your crew

00:43.418 --> 00:44.836
if you keep a good vibe on board

00:44.878 --> 00:46.296
as opposed to if
you're just a psycho bitch

00:46.338 --> 00:47.547
telling them what to do.

00:47.589 --> 00:48.548
They're gonna be
like [bleep] you.

00:48.590 --> 00:50.175
Hi, Mathew.

00:50.216 --> 00:51.176
You've worked for some
impressive people.

00:51.217 --> 00:53.053
Yeah.

00:53.094 --> 00:54.554
I've been a private chef for
Rupert Murdoch, Hugh Jackman.

00:54.596 --> 00:57.599
I'm always nervous
when I go into a new job.

00:57.640 --> 00:59.142
I just hope people like me.

00:59.184 --> 01:01.728
Terez, her husband
Lee, co-primaries;

01:01.770 --> 01:03.396
Clint and his fiancé, Karry.

01:03.438 --> 01:05.690
They decided to
have a wedding ceremony

01:05.732 --> 01:07.275
with their closest friends.

01:09.611 --> 01:11.404
-Is that whole truck full?
-Coming down the stairs.

01:11.446 --> 01:12.405
Coming up the stairs.

01:12.447 --> 01:14.074
Corner.

01:14.115 --> 01:16.451
The walk-ins are two floors
down a windy staircase.

01:18.286 --> 01:19.412
I'm not prepped at all.

01:19.454 --> 01:20.580
I hurt my knee last night.

01:20.622 --> 01:22.248
I'm freaked out.

01:22.290 --> 01:24.250
-Okay. So, what...
-I don't know what to do.

01:24.292 --> 01:25.627
I can't do this.

01:28.588 --> 01:29.756
Our chef injured himself.

01:29.798 --> 01:31.508
-There will be no chef?
-No chef?

01:31.549 --> 01:33.259
We need to make dinner.

01:34.886 --> 01:36.721
Whoa! Savage.

01:40.350 --> 01:42.143
This is why chefs are
always so angry.

01:46.189 --> 01:47.232
You can do better.

01:49.234 --> 01:50.860
Terrible.

01:51.903 --> 01:53.363
I have failed them.

02:02.664 --> 02:04.749
Girl, this is not okay.

02:04.791 --> 02:06.209
Did you taste dinner?

02:06.251 --> 02:09.671
That was terrible.

02:09.713 --> 02:10.922
Yes, unacceptable.

02:10.964 --> 02:13.550
I agree.
We didn't have a chef.

02:13.591 --> 02:15.593
-We're on a mega yacht.
-I get it.

02:15.635 --> 02:17.262
-Sorry, I...
-We're on a mega yacht!

02:17.303 --> 02:18.930
You're better than that,
so let's get that.

02:18.972 --> 02:20.473
Let's get the respect
we deserve.

02:20.515 --> 02:22.851
Hopefully I can sort this out.

02:22.892 --> 02:24.769
You got it.
You got it, Sandy.

02:24.811 --> 02:26.813
I've never been in this position
in my entire career.

02:26.855 --> 02:28.189
And you know why?
Because of COVID.

02:28.231 --> 02:29.566
Yeah.

02:29.607 --> 02:31.609
There's a seven
days' quarantine.

02:31.651 --> 02:32.610
Otherwise, I could get
a chef here.

02:32.652 --> 02:34.696
This is their wedding.

02:34.738 --> 02:36.489
I'm scared for them, and I'm
terrified what's gonna happen.

02:36.531 --> 02:38.283
We really are so easy to please.

02:38.324 --> 02:39.284
-We really are.
-I know.

02:39.325 --> 02:40.285
Come on, girl.

02:40.326 --> 02:41.286
We are on your team.

02:41.327 --> 02:42.287
All right, thank you.

02:42.328 --> 02:43.663
I get it.

02:43.705 --> 02:46.332
I don't have a chef,
I have a new crew.

02:46.374 --> 02:47.834
It's never easy
to hear criticism.

02:47.876 --> 02:49.377
I have to shoulder it.

02:49.419 --> 02:50.712
All I can do is try
to please tem.

02:55.008 --> 02:57.677
Unacceptable.
It's bullsh--.

02:57.719 --> 02:59.512
Night.

02:59.554 --> 03:00.513
Are you going to bed?

03:00.555 --> 03:01.514
-Yeah.
-Oh!

03:01.556 --> 03:02.515
Thank you so much for your help.

03:02.557 --> 03:04.267
That's okay.

03:04.309 --> 03:06.811
I'm more than happy to help
out in any department,

03:06.853 --> 03:08.980
but imagine
the disappointment of paying

03:09.022 --> 03:11.691
this huge amount of money
to find me in the galley,

03:11.733 --> 03:13.485
having anything to do
with your food.

03:17.697 --> 03:18.698
How you going?

03:18.740 --> 03:19.699
This is all clean.

03:19.741 --> 03:20.909
I wanna knock you off,

03:20.950 --> 03:22.744
and me and Lexi
will smash out the pans.

03:22.786 --> 03:24.412
Okay, cool.

03:24.454 --> 03:25.705
For breakfast, just do starter,
knife, and cutlery.

03:25.747 --> 03:27.374
Yeah.

03:27.415 --> 03:29.542
I mean, is he gonna be back
to do, like, a platter?

03:29.584 --> 03:30.543
I need to talk to Sandy.

03:30.585 --> 03:31.544
I don't know.

03:31.586 --> 03:33.380
Losing a chef...

03:33.421 --> 03:35.256
that's like losing a limb
in yachting world, you know?

03:35.298 --> 03:38.885
I am praying that Mathew will
come back, but I swear to God,

03:38.927 --> 03:40.970
I wanna strangle
his little head.

03:41.012 --> 03:42.347
Don't stress too much.

03:42.389 --> 03:43.556
Thank you.

03:47.477 --> 03:50.438
Was this a bad dream,
or did this really happen?

03:50.480 --> 03:51.606
I don't know.

03:51.648 --> 03:52.732
-Dinner was terrible.
-Yeah.

03:52.774 --> 03:53.858
-I get it.
-Yeah.

03:53.900 --> 03:55.443
[bleep]

03:55.485 --> 03:56.528
Don't make me a bad guy.

03:56.569 --> 03:59.447
Go, goodbye, out, out, out.

03:59.489 --> 04:02.242
So, he's coming back tomorrow,
right, for breakfast?

04:02.283 --> 04:03.618
Okay.

04:07.288 --> 04:08.248
Yeah.

04:08.289 --> 04:09.791
Ah.

04:09.833 --> 04:12.043
I've never seen this
in yachting, when the crew,

04:12.085 --> 04:15.005
who are not chefs,
have cooked for the guests.

04:15.046 --> 04:17.757
This is probably the biggest
disaster I've been faced with.

04:17.799 --> 04:19.843
And, like,
we've crashed tenders.

04:21.678 --> 04:22.804
No, I don't want you to do
anything for me.

04:22.846 --> 04:24.931
It's fine.

04:24.973 --> 04:26.016
We're gonna go dance.

04:26.057 --> 04:27.434
Going up to the top.

04:27.475 --> 04:28.977
It's bullsh--!

04:29.019 --> 04:31.021
I know, babe, but you're getting
mad at me for this trip.

04:31.062 --> 04:32.439
I'm not mad at you.

04:32.480 --> 04:33.606
We're not getting
our money back,

04:33.648 --> 04:34.649
it doesn't matter at this point.

04:34.691 --> 04:35.734
I don't give a sh--.

04:35.775 --> 04:36.985
-Babe, look at me.
-What?

04:37.027 --> 04:38.486
I love you.

04:39.487 --> 04:41.656
Woo!

04:43.825 --> 04:46.453
-Woot, woot, woot.
-Yeah!

04:46.494 --> 04:47.620
[neck cracks]

04:47.662 --> 04:48.788
Ow.

04:48.830 --> 04:50.040
First day of charter ever.

04:50.081 --> 04:51.666
It's in the books.

04:51.708 --> 04:53.793
Thank you so much for your
guidance and help today.

04:53.835 --> 04:55.337
Yeah, of course.
7:00 on deck.

04:55.378 --> 04:56.963
Lovely.

04:57.005 --> 04:59.466
Actually just happy to not
get fired on my first day...

05:03.845 --> 05:05.680
When I catch myself in a mirror,

05:05.722 --> 05:08.350
I'm like, oh, my hair
is, like sh--.

05:11.102 --> 05:12.479
-You were in a beauty pageant?
-I know. Yeah.

05:12.520 --> 05:13.688
What beauty pageant was it?

05:13.730 --> 05:15.315
-Miss Bahamas.
-You were Miss Bahamas?

05:15.357 --> 05:17.359
-Yes.
-That's so cool!

05:17.400 --> 05:20.403
Yeah, I went to Russia for
the Miss Universe title.

05:20.445 --> 05:21.571
Nice!

05:25.784 --> 05:26.951
Ooh.

05:31.039 --> 05:31.998
No.

05:32.040 --> 05:33.583
-Do it!
-Katie, come on.

05:33.625 --> 05:34.834
Oh, God.

05:35.919 --> 05:38.088
-Nice!
-She's flying!

05:38.129 --> 05:39.464
You know how to ride,
you know...

05:43.176 --> 05:44.761
You gotta lean forward on...
around it.

05:44.803 --> 05:47.013
-Yay!
-Yeah!

05:47.055 --> 05:48.890
That's how you do it!

05:48.932 --> 05:50.892
Yay!

05:50.934 --> 05:52.977
Whew.

05:53.019 --> 05:56.022
I was actually really impressed
how strong she was.

05:56.064 --> 05:57.399
You are yummy.

06:00.110 --> 06:03.530
Girl, you're the... you're...
girl, you're our girl.

06:03.571 --> 06:04.864
That's great.

06:04.906 --> 06:08.702
Top gun. Take me to be
or lose me forever.

06:08.743 --> 06:09.953
I'm ready for bed.

06:09.994 --> 06:13.915
Katie, tomorrow I will
lift you higher,

06:13.957 --> 06:15.542
and your legs will...

06:15.583 --> 06:17.585
I hope you guys sleep well.

06:19.713 --> 06:21.131
-Good night!
-Good night.

06:21.172 --> 06:23.550
-Good night, guys.
-Thank you so much.

06:27.512 --> 06:28.680
Nice, doing the log book.

06:28.722 --> 06:29.723
Yeah.

06:29.764 --> 06:30.724
Did you get some sleep?

06:30.765 --> 06:31.933
-A little bit.
-Cool.

06:31.975 --> 06:33.476
-All right, good night.
-All right.

06:33.518 --> 06:34.978
I've been at anchor on
smaller boats,

06:35.020 --> 06:36.813
and then before that,
all my previous jobs,

06:36.855 --> 06:38.815
I've been around lots
and lots of people.

06:38.857 --> 06:40.066
I spent four years selling cars,

06:40.108 --> 06:42.152
which was the worst time
of my life.

06:42.193 --> 06:44.112
On my first day, they pulled me
into the office

06:44.154 --> 06:45.905
when they heard one of my
phone calls,

06:45.947 --> 06:48.992
and they made me stay late,
stand on a table, on the phone,

06:49.034 --> 06:51.202
calling people while
people threw things at me,

06:51.244 --> 06:53.455
to make me smile while
I was speaking on the phone.

06:53.496 --> 06:56.499
That really sculpted
the way that I am today.

06:56.541 --> 06:57.834
At the time, it's hateful.

07:02.964 --> 07:05.842
Let's vacuum all this.
And do sky lounge, I think.

07:05.884 --> 07:07.093
Okay.

07:08.720 --> 07:10.930
All crew, all crew, that
is Malia off the radio.

07:10.972 --> 07:12.223
Okay.

07:20.690 --> 07:21.816
[bleep] I need to go to bed.

07:30.241 --> 07:31.618
Ooh, okay.

07:31.659 --> 07:33.161
I'm basically done vacuuming.

07:33.203 --> 07:34.746
-Okay.
-I'm gonna shoot off.

07:34.788 --> 07:36.081
-Are you all good?
-Yeah.

07:36.122 --> 07:38.041
Sweep, mop, and then going down.

07:38.083 --> 07:40.085
All right, thank you so much.

07:40.126 --> 07:41.628
Get some rest.

07:41.670 --> 07:43.963
Let's try!

07:44.005 --> 07:46.508
How the [bleep] are we
gonna survive the rest

07:46.549 --> 07:48.510
of the season if
this is day one?

07:48.551 --> 07:49.969
Like, you know,
some people can

07:50.011 --> 07:51.137
handle the pressure and
all that sh--.

07:51.179 --> 07:53.598
I don't want to,
but I can do it.

07:53.640 --> 07:55.642
I went to boarding school
when I was 13.

07:55.684 --> 07:58.269
I actually chose to go.

07:58.311 --> 08:00.146
I mean, it definitely
had its hard moments,

08:00.188 --> 08:02.065
but that's why I am
so independent,

08:02.107 --> 08:04.859
because, like, you know,
I didn't go back

08:04.901 --> 08:06.736
to my parents every
day after school.

08:06.778 --> 08:11.241
I just, yeah, went to a hostel
with a really psycho matron.

08:21.793 --> 08:22.961
Why?

08:28.133 --> 08:29.634
[phone vibrates]

08:29.676 --> 08:31.761
Hey, Mom,
it's 3:00 in the morning.

08:31.803 --> 08:33.138
I'm just going to bed.

08:33.179 --> 08:34.723
I'm used to working
hard on a charter,

08:34.764 --> 08:37.642
but this is, like, madness.

08:37.684 --> 08:39.978
I hate when people say
"Everything's gonna be okay."

08:40.020 --> 08:41.229
I really, really hate that.

08:41.271 --> 08:43.857
A couple months ago,
my dad died.

08:43.898 --> 08:46.693
He'd had, like,
a sudden brain aneurism,

08:46.735 --> 08:48.862
and my mom rushed him
to the hospital.

08:48.903 --> 08:50.530
Because it's a pandemic,

08:50.572 --> 08:52.699
you can't have your loved
one there with you.

08:52.741 --> 08:53.867
So, when she left and got home,

08:53.908 --> 08:55.285
that's when they called her

08:55.326 --> 08:56.286
and said, like,
"Well, he didn't make it."

08:56.327 --> 08:57.704
We were so confused.

08:57.746 --> 08:58.705
We were, like,
"What do you mean,

08:58.747 --> 08:59.706
he was just there, talking."

08:59.748 --> 09:01.207
I'm just tired.

09:02.834 --> 09:05.128
Talking about him makes me,
like, sad,

09:05.170 --> 09:08.214
because I haven't really grieved
the way I feel like I need to.

09:10.258 --> 09:12.052
I'll message you later.

09:12.093 --> 09:13.261
Love you, bye.

09:27.609 --> 09:28.902
Sh--.

09:32.364 --> 09:33.698
Hey.
Morning.

09:36.034 --> 09:37.243
Morning.

09:37.285 --> 09:38.370
What's it looking
like out there?

09:38.411 --> 09:39.621
Pretty horrendous.

09:40.789 --> 09:41.748
No.

09:41.790 --> 09:42.749
-Serious?
-Yeah.

09:42.791 --> 09:44.834
Oh [bleep].

09:44.876 --> 09:46.294
We're toast if he doesn't...

09:46.336 --> 09:47.879
well, we won't have any toast.

09:47.921 --> 09:49.339
I can do it.

09:49.381 --> 09:50.799
Get a cup of tea.

09:50.840 --> 09:52.384
We have a bachelor
party to throw.

09:52.425 --> 09:53.968
Yeah.

09:58.932 --> 10:00.392
-Morning.
-Hi.

10:00.433 --> 10:02.769
Can I get you a tea or coffee,
or anything?

10:02.811 --> 10:04.270
-Coffee would be nice.
-Coffee, yeah?

10:11.736 --> 10:13.029
No.

10:16.157 --> 10:17.283
Coffee!

10:22.330 --> 10:25.750
Who has a chef on backup
with seven days' quarantine?

10:25.792 --> 10:26.960
I have to figure this out.

10:28.837 --> 10:30.296
Please, God.

10:30.338 --> 10:31.881
Also, I need a deck stew,

10:31.923 --> 10:34.259
because I will
never be caught

10:34.300 --> 10:35.802
without a crewmember
in quarantine again.

10:35.844 --> 10:37.679
I learned my lesson.

10:37.721 --> 10:39.389
If you guys are hungry, I can
probably do some toasts, or...

10:41.182 --> 10:43.059
Some fruit? Yeah.

10:43.101 --> 10:45.437
That is the only time
I've ever been told that.

10:51.192 --> 10:52.861
I was just thinking
the same thing.

10:53.820 --> 10:55.071
Where's another knife?

10:55.113 --> 10:56.406
Up there.

11:04.122 --> 11:06.791
So, is he making breakfast,
is there a breakfast?

11:06.833 --> 11:08.960
Like, what's going on,
I'm so confused.

11:09.002 --> 11:11.004
[phone vibrates]

11:11.046 --> 11:13.089
Hey, Mathew, how are you?

11:23.475 --> 11:26.102
Hey, Mathew, how are you?

11:28.438 --> 11:29.939
and, uh...

11:39.491 --> 11:41.409
I'm glad you're okay,
first and foremost.

11:41.451 --> 11:42.410
Thank you.

11:42.452 --> 11:43.411
Will you be here for breakfast?

11:43.453 --> 11:44.954
-Yes.
-Okay, cool.

11:44.996 --> 11:46.164
-All right, thank you.
-Bye.

11:46.206 --> 11:47.832
Bye-bye.

11:47.874 --> 11:49.417
As a captain, I've had
fires on the Red Sea,

11:49.459 --> 11:52.879
I've faced pirates,
but no chef...

11:52.921 --> 11:53.922
that's, like, end game.

11:53.963 --> 11:55.423
So, the big question is,

11:55.465 --> 11:59.427
is Mathew capable of continuing
in the charter season?

11:59.469 --> 12:01.888
Yes!

12:01.930 --> 12:04.349
All crew, all crew,
our chef is returning.

12:04.391 --> 12:07.102
-Thank the Lord.
-Hallelujah.

12:08.812 --> 12:10.438
Morning, how was
your gym workout?

12:10.480 --> 12:11.564
It was good, thank you.

12:17.904 --> 12:19.531
Yeah.
I think Malia's great.

12:19.572 --> 12:21.157
Like, really, really great.

12:21.199 --> 12:23.910
Thanks for taking care of
everything this morning.

12:26.204 --> 12:27.956
I think it's gonna be
like this all day, so...

12:27.997 --> 12:29.040
Yeah.

12:30.583 --> 12:31.960
Oh, why didn't you come get me?

12:32.002 --> 12:33.003
They've all just been up.

12:33.044 --> 12:34.045
Are they okay, though, or...

12:34.087 --> 12:36.297
Yeah, they're fine.

12:36.339 --> 12:40.176
All crew, all crew,
water taxi approaching.

12:40.218 --> 12:41.344
Hopefully that is our chef.

12:41.386 --> 12:42.929
[bleep] yeah.

12:42.971 --> 12:44.514
Could you guys meet him
on the swim platform?

12:44.556 --> 12:45.515
[bleep]

12:45.557 --> 12:47.183
Hey!

12:47.225 --> 12:48.476
Chef's on board.

12:48.518 --> 12:49.477
-Good morning.
-Welcome back!

12:49.519 --> 12:51.187
Thank you!

12:51.229 --> 12:52.313
Let me go get changed,
and I'll get right to it.

12:52.355 --> 12:53.398
-Okay, awesome.
-Welcome back.

12:53.440 --> 12:54.399
-Hey, good morning!
-Hey.

12:54.441 --> 12:57.152
Morning.

12:57.193 --> 12:58.153
-Good morning, Katie.
-Good morning, Katie.

12:58.194 --> 12:59.404
How did you guys sleep?

12:59.446 --> 13:00.989
We slept good,
thank you for asking.

13:01.031 --> 13:02.032
-I slept good, yeah.
-Yeah?

13:02.073 --> 13:03.074
Yeah.

13:03.116 --> 13:04.534
All right...

13:04.576 --> 13:06.494
How are you, how's your knee,
what happened?

13:06.536 --> 13:08.913
It wasn't anything serious, but
I'm in a little bit of pain.

13:08.955 --> 13:10.373
Are the guests up?

13:10.415 --> 13:12.125
Yeah, they'll probably
want some food soon.

13:12.167 --> 13:13.460
I'll get some avo toast going.

13:13.501 --> 13:16.504
I have this deep
anxiety inside of me

13:16.546 --> 13:18.590
before that first meal
for a new guest,

13:18.631 --> 13:22.135
and instead of just getting over
that and doing it, I bailed.

13:24.387 --> 13:26.306
I'm gonna do the fruit ASAP.

13:26.348 --> 13:29.059
Two jobs in the past,
I have actually left

13:29.100 --> 13:32.145
before I started
because of anxiety.

13:32.187 --> 13:34.606
It's something I need
and want to overcome.

13:34.647 --> 13:36.900
I'm very sorry for the delay.

13:38.068 --> 13:39.444
Good morning.

13:39.486 --> 13:41.529
Is it all right if
I just plate and egg this

