26:18.161 --> 26:19.454
Happy you're here, Mat.

26:19.496 --> 26:20.455
You can come stay
in our cabin tonight.

26:20.497 --> 26:21.956
Wholly redeemed himself.

26:21.998 --> 26:22.957
-Yeah.
-He did.

26:22.999 --> 26:24.501
-Yum!
-Mm!

26:27.045 --> 26:28.046
Okay.

26:28.088 --> 26:29.339
You good?

26:29.381 --> 26:30.423
Yeah.

26:31.800 --> 26:32.801
Yeah, ish.

26:32.842 --> 26:33.802
Little hesitation there.

26:33.843 --> 26:34.803
-Ish.
-Ish?

26:34.844 --> 26:37.097
-Ish.
-Why?

26:37.138 --> 26:39.391
I think obviously just
the more I practice things,

26:39.432 --> 26:41.142
obviously the more naturally
it will come.

26:41.184 --> 26:42.435
Yeah.

26:47.524 --> 26:49.401
So, always think of the loop.

26:49.442 --> 26:51.111
Ah, and then that becomes...

26:52.070 --> 26:53.780
Yeah, hold the loop,

26:53.822 --> 26:56.241
and then control it with how
much line I have here.

26:58.576 --> 27:00.078
All right, Z, I'm gonna
leave you

27:00.120 --> 27:01.079
in charge of the swim platform.

27:01.121 --> 27:02.539
Okay.

27:02.580 --> 27:03.748
Will you just radio me if
any guests come down?

27:03.790 --> 27:04.749
Sure.

27:04.791 --> 27:06.793
Yeah, come play around, tinker.

27:06.835 --> 27:08.378
That was delicious,
but I'm gonna call it.

27:08.420 --> 27:09.838
I'm good.

27:09.879 --> 27:10.839
I could eat a hundred
more mussels.

27:10.880 --> 27:12.215
We've got dessert.

27:12.257 --> 27:14.259
Z, please keep an eye
on the jet ski line.

27:14.300 --> 27:15.385
<i>Copy that.</i>

27:17.846 --> 27:19.264
-Chef?
-Yes, darling?

27:19.305 --> 27:20.348
Could you help me deliver
these to the guests?

27:20.390 --> 27:21.766
I'd do anything for you.

27:21.808 --> 27:23.018
I just love you.

27:23.059 --> 27:24.227
-Do you really?
-I do.

27:24.269 --> 27:25.437
You always lie to the chef.

27:25.478 --> 27:27.230
Tell the chef you love them,

27:27.272 --> 27:28.940
because they'll always
serve you, like, spare food.

27:28.982 --> 27:30.483
You're a sweetheart.

27:30.525 --> 27:32.110
That's bad, I guess
that's leading people on,

27:32.152 --> 27:33.570
knowing it's gonna go nowhere.

27:33.611 --> 27:35.822
But, like, I'm a born flirter.

27:35.864 --> 27:37.574
Because you're flirting
with me and I'm bored,

27:37.615 --> 27:38.867
I have nothing else to do,
I'll flirt back.

27:38.908 --> 27:40.326
I actually told a guy that.

27:40.368 --> 27:42.078
He was, like,
"I accept that, that's fine."

27:42.120 --> 27:44.581
Like, seriously, most chefs
are ----ing assholes.

27:44.622 --> 27:46.207
I'll try to keep
it positive.

27:46.249 --> 27:47.876
Yeah.

27:50.628 --> 27:51.963
Yay!

27:52.005 --> 27:53.256
Delicious chocolate mousse
for you.

27:53.298 --> 27:57.093
-Whoa!
-Thank you!

27:57.135 --> 27:59.304
You're welcome, thank you.

27:59.346 --> 28:00.472
Mm!

28:00.513 --> 28:01.890
Everything was on point.

28:01.931 --> 28:03.475
Look what
a beautiful day it is!

28:03.516 --> 28:05.060
Woo!

28:12.984 --> 28:14.194
Sh--.

28:14.235 --> 28:15.445
And then tomorrow's
the wedding.

28:15.487 --> 28:16.446
Nice lunch?

28:16.488 --> 28:19.157
-We did.
-Cool.

28:19.199 --> 28:20.533
Did they like their lunch?

28:20.575 --> 28:21.618
Yeah, no, they were really,
really happy.

28:21.659 --> 28:23.119
Oh, yay!

28:23.161 --> 28:24.162
And they said compliments
to the chef.

28:24.204 --> 28:25.330
Oh, awesome, awesome.

28:25.372 --> 28:26.581
All good vibes.

28:26.623 --> 28:28.333
-All right, thank you.
-Keep it there.

28:28.375 --> 28:29.334
All right!

28:29.376 --> 28:30.335
Just make it fun.

28:30.377 --> 28:31.920
Yeah.

28:31.961 --> 28:33.296
Bullsh-- with them,
get them drunk, happy.

28:33.338 --> 28:34.422
Bachelor party, yeah.

28:34.464 --> 28:35.423
I'll do me best.

28:35.465 --> 28:37.050
I have faith.

28:37.092 --> 28:38.426
All right, boys,
let's go catch dinner.

28:38.468 --> 28:40.095
Gentlemen, let's get
you loaded up.

28:40.136 --> 28:41.096
Get some fish!

28:41.137 --> 28:42.430
Hey...

28:42.472 --> 28:45.350
hey, is that jet ski
tied onto something?

28:45.392 --> 28:47.185
I don't think it is.

28:47.227 --> 28:48.978
-Ugh!
-I think it's floating away.

28:49.020 --> 28:50.522
Get a life jacket on,
let's go grab that jet ski.

28:50.563 --> 28:53.066
Oh [bleep].

28:55.068 --> 28:56.361
Get on with Lloyd, please.

28:58.029 --> 28:59.447
Coming up...

28:59.489 --> 29:02.158
I keep forgetting
we have a wedding, still.

29:11.751 --> 29:11.960
Ugh.

29:13.962 --> 29:16.339
Get a lifejacket on, please,
let's go grab that jet ski.

29:22.512 --> 29:25.098
Get on with Lloyd please.

29:25.140 --> 29:26.474
Just another day in paradise.

29:26.516 --> 29:27.976
I looked out there,
and I was like, dude,

29:28.018 --> 29:29.477
that looks a little far.

29:36.735 --> 29:39.946
All right, your stern's clear.

29:39.988 --> 29:41.281
Bridge, bridge,
that is tender away.

29:41.322 --> 29:43.074
-Copy.
-Woo!

29:43.116 --> 29:45.285
For the bachelorette party,
we have guests heading down

29:45.326 --> 29:47.078
to the swim platform
to use the unicorn.

29:48.538 --> 29:50.290
That's okay.

29:50.331 --> 29:52.083
I'm gonna let him off the hook
just this first time,

29:52.125 --> 29:55.086
because I've also tied
a line wrong

29:55.128 --> 29:57.172
and watched
the jet ski float away,

29:57.213 --> 30:00.258
so I think it's like
a rite of passage on deck.

30:00.300 --> 30:02.385
Oh, my God, this is so cute!

30:02.427 --> 30:04.637
We named her Maureen.

30:04.679 --> 30:06.306
It's a bachelor party!

30:06.348 --> 30:09.142
My last night!

30:09.184 --> 30:11.311
Yeah.

30:11.353 --> 30:12.437
Just down that little dirt path.

30:12.479 --> 30:13.646
Wow, dude, look
at this water.

30:13.688 --> 30:15.565
-It's beautiful.
-Yes!

30:15.607 --> 30:19.194
-That is a bachelorette...
-That's a party.

30:19.235 --> 30:20.570
You ladies like any snacks
or anything like that?

30:22.197 --> 30:24.282
That's a good snack.

30:24.324 --> 30:25.784
Clint, you excited
about tomorrow?

30:25.825 --> 30:27.160
-Hell, yeah, brother.
-Big day!

30:27.202 --> 30:28.703
My life is officially over.

30:30.538 --> 30:31.748
Bottle of vodka.

30:31.790 --> 30:34.751
-Yay, thank you.
-Pleasure.

30:34.793 --> 30:36.461
Having a hospitality background,

30:36.503 --> 30:38.672
I am very comfortable,
especially if people are drunk.

30:38.713 --> 30:40.674
You see them in
restaurants every day.

30:40.715 --> 30:42.300
So, probably the first thing

30:42.342 --> 30:43.677
that I'm feeling
super confident with.

30:43.718 --> 30:45.679
Nice job, Z.
Go take a break!

30:45.720 --> 30:46.721
Thank you.

30:48.181 --> 30:49.557
It's so beautiful here.

30:52.227 --> 30:53.395
I know, right?

31:02.654 --> 31:05.824
But seriously, they honestly say
that that would be gold-digging.

31:05.865 --> 31:07.492
So, should I just date a bum?

31:07.534 --> 31:09.703
I used to date, like,
for love and all that sh--

31:09.744 --> 31:11.705
but love don't pay
the ----ing bills.

31:11.746 --> 31:12.706
So dumb.

31:12.747 --> 31:14.290
I feel ya, bro.

31:14.332 --> 31:15.500
Have you seen any
[bleep]s swimming around?

31:15.542 --> 31:16.501
-No.
-I haven't, either.

31:16.543 --> 31:18.503
Ooh.

31:18.545 --> 31:19.796
-Let me see.
-Hey!

31:19.838 --> 31:20.797
A sea cucumber!

31:20.839 --> 31:22.549
-Oh!
-Sick.

31:22.590 --> 31:23.591
Weird.

31:29.681 --> 31:31.349
<i>Malia, Malia, Dave,</i>
<i>just a request.</i>

31:31.391 --> 31:32.726
Has the chef got a fish,

31:32.767 --> 31:34.519
so the boys can have
a picture with a fish?

31:38.773 --> 31:40.400
<i>Copy, tender returning.</i>

31:40.442 --> 31:41.401
Can I just leave this
with you guys,

31:41.443 --> 31:42.444
can you bring it back to me?

31:42.485 --> 31:44.612
-Yeah.
-Thank you.

31:44.654 --> 31:45.822
-Yes!
-Yeah!

31:45.864 --> 31:48.533
Woo!

31:48.575 --> 31:50.118
-Okay, boys.
-Great, thank you.

31:50.160 --> 31:51.619
Thank you very much!
Man, that was fun.

31:51.661 --> 31:53.163
Do you want
a photo with your fish?

31:53.204 --> 31:54.789
-Yeah, yeah, yeah!
-Cool.

31:54.831 --> 31:56.583
-Yeah!
-Woo!

31:56.624 --> 31:57.834
That was fun,
it was a great experience.

31:57.876 --> 31:59.419
Yeah, now that's a catch.

31:59.461 --> 32:01.212
I actually quite like
walking on these things.

32:01.254 --> 32:02.881
It's like being in a
play park when you were a kid,

32:02.922 --> 32:05.425
but even better,
when you're an adult!

32:05.467 --> 32:07.385
Oh, did they actually catch it?

32:07.427 --> 32:08.428
No.

32:08.470 --> 32:09.512
Oh, I was, like...

32:09.554 --> 32:11.723
Yeah, it came gutted and scaled.

32:11.765 --> 32:15.393
Babe, are you ready
to say your "I dos" tomorrow?

32:15.435 --> 32:17.604
I am. I am.

32:17.645 --> 32:18.813
So excited.

32:18.855 --> 32:20.106
Okay, clear to come up?

32:20.148 --> 32:21.107
Yeah.

32:21.149 --> 32:23.318
Coming up.

32:23.360 --> 32:24.611
Lloyd, wanna drive it?

32:24.652 --> 32:26.404
-Yeah, sweet.
-I'll do the cable.

32:27.906 --> 32:29.366
Looking good.

32:29.407 --> 32:31.451
All crew, all crew,
dinner's ready.

32:31.493 --> 32:33.161
-Thank you for that.
-You're welcome.

32:33.203 --> 32:34.496
Oh, I'll fix your collar.

32:34.537 --> 32:35.705
Thank you.

32:35.747 --> 32:36.790
-You like it like...
-Pop my collar?

32:36.831 --> 32:38.458
Yeah.

32:38.500 --> 32:39.459
Only when I'm trying
to impress the ladies.

32:39.501 --> 32:40.794
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

32:40.835 --> 32:42.837
So, yeah, so when
we're on charter,

32:42.879 --> 32:44.881
it's lunch and dinner
for the crew, okay?

32:44.923 --> 32:46.466
Copy, yeah.

32:46.508 --> 32:47.467
Because they're working
really hard, and...

32:47.509 --> 32:49.260
Yep, all right.

32:49.302 --> 32:50.512
-Thank you so much, sandy.
-Okay, you're welcome.

32:50.553 --> 32:51.513
I appreciate how
understanding you are.

32:51.554 --> 32:53.181
No worries.

32:53.223 --> 32:54.474
I knew Mathew would come
around to making crew food,

32:54.516 --> 32:56.476
and I just had
to play my cards right.

32:56.518 --> 32:58.937
I just had to take it
one step at a time,

32:58.978 --> 33:01.231
and let him settle back in.

33:01.272 --> 33:02.857
Hi, welcome back.

33:04.693 --> 33:06.361
I can't hear anything.

33:23.420 --> 33:24.421
Here, I'll sit here.

33:24.462 --> 33:26.256
Yeah, we're good.

33:26.297 --> 33:27.257
They're all main deck aft.

33:27.298 --> 33:28.258
Did you check on them just now?

33:28.299 --> 33:29.801
Yeah.

33:29.843 --> 33:31.761
-I'll keep an eye on them.
-I appreciate it a lot.

33:31.803 --> 33:33.763
Do you want a cup of tea?
Makes everything better.

33:33.805 --> 33:35.181
Is there any Earl Grey?

33:35.223 --> 33:36.349
There is Earl Grey.

33:36.391 --> 33:37.517
-Go on, darling.
-Oh!

33:37.559 --> 33:39.436
Okay, I'm gonna go get changed.

33:39.477 --> 33:41.730
Katie is lovely, but I don't
get to speak to her that much.

33:41.771 --> 33:43.898
She's also chief stew,
so she's scary.

33:50.238 --> 33:51.489
Can you get two?

33:51.531 --> 33:53.199
[bleep] you, Dave,
I'm not weak!

33:53.241 --> 33:54.242
It is quite difficult,
especially when you've got

33:54.284 --> 33:56.786
short T. Rex arms.

33:56.828 --> 33:58.663
Do you think I should
put it underneath?

33:58.705 --> 34:00.290
Yeah, I like it,
and then make sure

34:00.331 --> 34:02.292
they're always in
the middle of the chair.

34:02.334 --> 34:03.877
So, it's nice and even.

34:03.918 --> 34:06.880
My last boat, I still had,
like, seven girls under me,

34:06.921 --> 34:08.548
but you could always use more.

34:08.590 --> 34:10.717
The bigger size you get,

34:10.759 --> 34:12.969
slightly less hands-on
the chief stew is,

34:13.011 --> 34:14.804
because there's
so much more admin.

34:14.846 --> 34:16.639
But hey, I'm not afraid
to get my hands dirty.

34:16.681 --> 34:18.433
I still like it,
it's a challenge.

34:18.475 --> 34:19.976
And I've got my third stew

34:20.018 --> 34:23.021
and I've got a chef back,
so let's do this.

34:25.440 --> 34:26.775
-Not bad.
-You're vibing?

34:26.816 --> 34:28.443
The vibe is the vibe.

34:28.485 --> 34:29.778
Vibe check.

34:31.613 --> 34:33.281
Okay, see you in the morning.

34:33.323 --> 34:34.824
I'll see you in the morning.

34:34.866 --> 34:36.868
-Get you tied up.
-Tie me, baby.

34:38.328 --> 34:39.412
Beautiful, baby.

34:39.454 --> 34:40.622
Let's do it.

34:40.663 --> 34:42.457
Ooh, it's raining.

34:44.459 --> 34:45.794
There we go.

34:47.962 --> 34:49.422
[thunder]

34:50.465 --> 34:52.258
Oh!

34:52.300 --> 34:53.677
Y'all need to cover
these cushions?

34:56.638 --> 34:57.847
Mother----er.

34:57.889 --> 34:59.933
Cushions.

34:59.974 --> 35:01.434
Deck crew, deck crew,
I don't know if you know,

35:01.476 --> 35:02.686
but it's pissing down
with rain.

35:03.770 --> 35:05.355
Copy.
Z, can you gimme a hand?

35:05.397 --> 35:07.607
Is your seat wet?

35:07.649 --> 35:08.858
The other guy
should be helping.

35:08.900 --> 35:10.360
Ah, ah, ah!

35:14.656 --> 35:16.783
Oh [bleep]!

35:16.825 --> 35:18.451
Galley, galley, we're good
to go when you are.

35:18.493 --> 35:19.577
Roger dodger, 10-4.

35:19.619 --> 35:21.371
Going into the first dinner,

35:21.413 --> 35:25.083
I just wanna redeem myself
and not overcomplicate things.

35:25.125 --> 35:26.918
So, I know I can do this,

35:26.960 --> 35:28.712
but I need to prove
to the guests

35:28.753 --> 35:30.797
and the captain and the crew
that I can do this.

35:30.839 --> 35:32.632
We're gonna synchronize
the service.

35:32.674 --> 35:34.551
Me and you will both take three,
and you'll take two.

35:34.592 --> 35:35.802
Yeah.

35:35.844 --> 35:37.637
I will plate the three
on this side.

35:37.679 --> 35:39.597
By the time she gets
to her...

35:39.639 --> 35:41.725
To her end, we'll already...

35:41.766 --> 35:43.059
Okay.

35:43.101 --> 35:45.020
Synchronization is
so ----ing important.

35:45.061 --> 35:47.731
I don't know why people bring
out dishes two at a time.

35:47.772 --> 35:50.358
Like, on a superyacht, you
should have the best service.

35:50.400 --> 35:52.068
That's what guests like,
they like a show.

35:52.110 --> 35:54.612
And also, I just think
it looks good.

35:54.654 --> 35:55.697
I love truffle pasta!

35:55.739 --> 35:56.990
I'm here to impress you.

35:57.032 --> 35:58.116
The water was not cold.

35:58.158 --> 35:59.868
No, it's the air temp.

35:59.909 --> 36:01.536
It's when you get outta
the water that it's cold.

36:03.371 --> 36:04.789
Darling, you look so gorgeous.

36:04.831 --> 36:06.332
Woo-ooh!

36:06.374 --> 36:08.460
For your starter tonight,
truffle pasta.

36:08.501 --> 36:10.086
-Yeah!
-Woo!

36:10.128 --> 36:11.963
It smells so good.

36:12.005 --> 36:13.381
I will eat the rest of this.

36:13.423 --> 36:14.591
Oh, my gosh, that was amazing.

36:14.632 --> 36:16.926
-Awesome.
-Mm!

36:16.968 --> 36:18.553
This is my favorite thing
I've eaten all week.

36:22.057 --> 36:23.350
And then go into the laundry.

36:23.391 --> 36:24.601
-Mm-hmm.
-Okay, cool.

36:24.642 --> 36:26.061
How's your knee feeling today?

36:26.102 --> 36:27.354
-Sore, but, like...
-Yeah.

36:27.395 --> 36:28.688
It's mostly on stairs.

36:28.730 --> 36:29.689
But you can, like,
put weight on it?

36:29.731 --> 36:31.149
Yeah, yeah.

36:31.191 --> 36:34.152
Well, I am pretty skeptical
of chefs nowadays.

36:34.194 --> 36:37.989
I think the extent
to which he's physically hurt...

36:38.031 --> 36:39.699
not so much.

36:39.741 --> 36:40.700
I thought
we were gonna lose you there.

36:40.742 --> 36:41.993
Oh, my God.

36:42.035 --> 36:43.411
We're gonna synchronize
the service.

36:43.453 --> 36:44.662
Mat throws it down.

36:44.704 --> 36:46.956
Mat's the sh--.

36:46.998 --> 36:48.083
Loving the pasta.

36:48.124 --> 36:50.543
Oh, my gosh, mission accomp...

36:50.585 --> 36:52.003
well... I don't wanna
speak too soon;

36:52.045 --> 36:53.713
we got two more courses to go.

36:58.593 --> 37:00.845
Woop!
Oh, my God.

37:00.887 --> 37:01.846
Whoa!

37:01.888 --> 37:03.098
Getting a little windy out here.

37:03.139 --> 37:04.933
There's a little blanket
right there.

37:04.974 --> 37:05.934
I'll get us a blanket,
or I'll get you something.

37:05.975 --> 37:07.060
It's ----ing chilly.

37:10.063 --> 37:11.731
-Freezing.
-I don't wanna do this.

37:11.773 --> 37:12.941
-Ah!
-Oh-oh!

37:12.982 --> 37:14.734
-Getting nasty.
-Let's go inside.

37:14.776 --> 37:17.195
Galley, you need to stand by, we
have to move everything inside.

37:17.237 --> 37:19.197
Girls, can I have
a hand up here?

37:19.239 --> 37:20.532
Let's go, babe, come on.

37:22.617 --> 37:23.910
Yo, Lex, can we bring these?

37:23.952 --> 37:25.662
No, we can't,
they're not seated yet.

37:25.704 --> 37:28.748
-Three minutes.
-Three minutes?

37:28.790 --> 37:31.668
I tried so ----ing hard to
make everything perfect today,

37:31.710 --> 37:34.004
and my whole dinner service
could be ----ed.

37:34.045 --> 37:35.755
The more obstacles, the better.

37:35.797 --> 37:38.091
I can't wait to see
how Mat cooks it up.

37:44.305 --> 37:45.098
<i>Galley, you need to stand by,</i>

37:46.683 --> 37:47.684
<i>we have to move</i>
<i>everything inside.</i>

37:49.227 --> 37:51.146
All right, this needs
to go while it's hot.

37:51.187 --> 37:53.565
Go to your spot,
babe, babe, babe...

37:53.606 --> 37:55.191
<i>Courtney, Courtney,</i>
<i>are you downstairs?</i>

37:55.233 --> 37:57.277
Just setting out the placemats.

37:57.318 --> 37:58.820
Okay, I'll help her downstairs.

37:58.862 --> 38:00.280
The universe started
----ing with us

38:00.321 --> 38:01.948
from day one on this trip.

38:01.990 --> 38:04.534
Not having a chef, these
guests are drinking like...

38:04.576 --> 38:06.786
The weather is a ----ing
sh--show,

38:06.828 --> 38:10.165
and it's like, oh, how much
more [bleep]s can I give?

38:10.206 --> 38:11.666
How much longer till the food?

38:11.708 --> 38:13.084
I don't know.

38:13.126 --> 38:14.711
